{
  "_README": "Model alias registry (design.md §1.2.4). One entry per canonical model; `canonical_id` is the join key for the deprecation/EOL calendar and per-stack Pro matching — the calendar shows one row per canonical model with per-provider EOL columns, never double-counting. `aliases` maps a provider namespace to the exact model ids that namespace uses for this model, including dated snapshot ids. Namespace keys: anthropic, openai, azure-openai, google-gemini, google-vertex, aws-bedrock, mistral, xai, openrouter, litellm. Seed sources: Anthropic's docs model table (which lists Anthropic/Bedrock/Vertex ids), OpenRouter /api/v1/models ids, LiteLLM model_prices_and_context_window.json keys. MAINTENANCE: (1) alias lists are append-only — never delete an id once observed in the wild; retired ids are still needed to resolve historical events; (2) when a collector sees a model id matching no alias, it opens an exceptions-queue item and the id is mapped here (new entry or new alias) before the event publishes; (3) `headline: true` marks models whose price.changed events are sev1 per schemas/severity.json — review the flag when a successor family ships; (4) edits go through CI schema validation and code review like any registry change; (5) ids below were seeded 2026-07-06 from public provider docs and must be re-verified against live collector output when collectors first run.",
